<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text"><p>I'm using a custom BaseView, which extends Backbone's remove method:</p>

<pre><code>app.BaseView = Backbone.View.extend({

    views: [], // array to keep a ref of child-views for proper disposal later on

    remove: function() {

        // dispose any sub-views
        if (_.isArray(this.views) &amp;&amp; this.views.length &gt; 0) {
            _.each(this.views, function(view) {
                view.remove();
            });
        }

        // if the inheriting class defines a custom on-remove method, call it!
        if (_.isFunction(this.onRemove)) {
            this.onRemove();
        }

        // unbind all events from this view
        this.off();

        // finally, call Backbone's default remove method to
        // remove the view from the DOM
        Backbone.View.prototype.remove.call(this);
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p>There's still a catch: models and collections need to be disposed by hand, because you don't know if it's used by other views too.</p>
</div>
